>[Question]
>There are two floating-point numbers, find the value of their
>difference divided by their product.
>
>
>
>[Difficulty]
>I do not understand what is ment by product, and how to get it.  
>Please help...
>
>[Thoughts]

The product of two numbers is the result of multiplying them. The 
difference is actually the trickier part: by convention we mean the 
result of subtracting the *smaller* number from the *larger* number.

- Doctor Rick, The Math Forum
  <http://mathforum.org/dr.math/>

